{"title":"{{< i18n stakeholder_register >}}","markdown":{"headingText":"{{< i18n stakeholder_register >}}","headingAttr":{"id":"","classes":[],"keyvalue":[]},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n## Purpose of This Document\n\nThis Stakeholder Register identifies and classifies all key stakeholders\ninvolved in, or impacted by, the **Subsea Benthic Analysis AI project**,\ndefining:\n\n- Roles and responsibilities\n- Level of interest and influence\n- Engagement strategy\n- Decision authority\n\nThis document is a **mandatory PMBOK artifact** and must be approved **before\nfinalization of the Project Management Plan (PMP)**.\n\n---\n\n## Stakeholder Classification Principles\n\nStakeholders are classified according to:\n\n- **Influence**: ability to affect decisions or outcomes  \n- **Interest**: level of concern with project results  \n- **Authority**: decision or validation power  \n\nEnvironmental and ecological stakeholders are treated as **primary\nstakeholders**, regardless of organizational hierarchy.\n\n---\n\n## Stakeholder Register\n\n| ID | Stakeholder | Organization / Unit | Role in Project | Interest | Influence | Primary Responsibility | Engagement Strategy |\n|----|------------|---------------------|-----------------|----------|-----------|------------------------|--------------------|\n| S1 | Project Sponsor | NOAA / SUB / Petrobras | Strategic Sponsor | High | High | Strategic direction, funding, final approvals | Executive reviews, Stage‑Gates |\n| S2 | Environmental SMEs | NOAA / SUB | Scientific Authority | High | High | Ecological validation, acceptance authority | Continuous validation, reviews |\n| S3 | Product Owner (PO) | NOAA / SUB | Business & Value Owner | High | High | OKR alignment, prioritization, value tracking | Weekly checkpoints |\n| S4 | Project Manager | SUB | Delivery Authority | High | Medium | Planning, execution, reporting | Daily coordination |\n| S5 | Data Science Lead | SUB / TIC | Technical Authority | Medium | Medium | Model design, performance decisions | Technical reviews |\n| S6 | Data Engineering Lead | SUB / TIC | Pipeline & Data Authority | Medium | Medium | Data ingestion, versioning, infrastructure | Sprint alignment |\n| S7 | IT / Infrastructure | Petrobras IT | Platform Support | Low | Medium | Compute, storage, security | Resource planning |\n| S8 | Environmental Governance | SUB / Compliance | Oversight & Audit | Medium | High | Environmental compliance, auditability | Formal checkpoints |\n| S9 | Operations / AUV Teams | SUB / Operations | Data Providers | Medium | Low | Image acquisition, metadata accuracy | On-demand alignment |\n| S10 | Executive Management | Petrobras | Oversight | Low | High | Strategic visibility, escalation | Executive briefings |\n\n---\n\n## Stakeholder Influence vs Interest Matrix (Summary)\n\n| Category | Stakeholders |\n|--------|--------------|\n| High Influence / High Interest | Sponsor, Environmental SMEs, PO |\n| High Influence / Low Interest | Executive Management, Compliance |\n| Low Influence / High Interest | Data Science, Data Engineering |\n| Low Influence / Low Interest | Operations (AUV Teams) |\n\n---\n\n## Key Stakeholder Roles and Decision Rights\n\n### Environmental SMEs (NOAA / SUB)\n- Final authority on ecological validity\n- Approval power at ecological Stage‑Gates (G1, G2)\n- Veto right if ecological risk is identified\n\n### Project Sponsor (NOAA / SUB)\n- Go / No‑Go authority at all Stage‑Gates\n- Final approval of scope, budget, and scaling\n\n### Product Owner (PO)\n- Owns [OKR at section @sec-okr]\n- Validates business and environmental value delivery\n- Prioritizes backlog based on ecological impact\n\n---\n\n## Stakeholder Risks and Mitigation\n\n| Risk | Stakeholder | Mitigation |\n|----|------------|------------|\n| Ecological trust erosion | Environmental SMEs | Early and continuous involvement |\n| Misalignment on value | Sponsor / PO | OKR and KPI transparency |\n| Technical over-optimization | Data Science | Stage‑Gates with ecological KPIs |\n| Adoption resistance | Operations | Early communication |\n\n---\n\n## Stakeholder Engagement Cadence (High-Level)\n\n| Stakeholder Group | Engagement Type | Frequency |\n|------------------|-----------------|-----------|\n| Sponsor | Executive review | Monthly / Gates |\n| Environmental SMEs | Validation workshops | Weekly / Bi-weekly |\n| PO & PM | Alignment checkpoints | ≥ 2× per week |\n| Technical Team | Delivery sync | Weekly |\n| Compliance / Governance | Audit checkpoints | As required |\n\n---\n\n## Approval and Baseline\n\nThis Stakeholder Register is considered **baselined** upon approval and must be\nupdated via formal change control if stakeholder roles, influence, or authority\nchange.\n\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":true,"code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"fo